layout.p:
Columns: 1;
                                                  ruled lines: 17;
                                                  written lines: 17; Uniform layout. Visible pricking; ruling executed with hard-point on the hair-side of the leaf.Writing in one column, with masoretic punctuation and masorah magna and parva. Masorah magna in one line of the upper and of the lower margin, where it sometimes creates a round corner.The beginning of a weekly section marked by an ornamental פ, and the liturgical subdivisions marked by Hebrew letters in the margins.
